quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  12,87,My sons! Seek news of Yusuf and his brother. Do not despair of solace from Allah. No one despairs of solace from Allah except for people who are kafirun.´
  12,88,"So when they came into his presence, they said, ´Your Eminence! Hardship has hit us and our families. We bring scant merchandise, but fill the measure for us generously. Allah always rewards a generous giver.´"
  12,89,"He said, ´Are you aware of what you did to Yusuf and his brother in ignorance?´"
  12,90,"They said, ´Are you Yusuf?´ He said, ´I am indeed Yusuf, and this here is my brother. Allah has acted graciously to us. As for those who fear Allah and are steadfast, Allah does not allow to go to waste the wage of any people who do good.´"
  12,91,"They said, ´By Allah, Allah has favoured you above us. Clearly we were in the wrong.´"
  12,92,"He said, ´No blame at all will fall on you. Today you have forgiveness from Allah. He is the Most Merciful of the merciful"
  12,93,Go with this shirt of mine and cast it on my father´s face and he will see again. Then come to me with all your families.´
  12,94,"And when the caravan went on its way, their father said, ´I can smell Yusuf´s scent! You probably think I have become senile.´"
  12,95,"They said, ´By Allah! Your mind is still astray.´"